<page>
   <topic>*REVERSE_WORDS Function</topic>
    <description>Reverse the order of words in a string - default delimiter is cr-lf.</description>
   <syntax>New_List as C = *REVERSE_WORDS(C string[,C delimiter])</syntax>
   <arguments>
     <argument>
         <name>New_List</name>
         <description>A delimited list of entries.</description>
     </argument>
     <argument>
         <name>string</name>
         <description>A delimited list of entries.</description>
     </argument>
     <argument>
         <name>delimiter</name>
         <description>Optional. Default = CR-LF. The character(s) that separate the list entries.</description>
     </argument>
   </arguments>
  
   <discussion>
The *REVERSE_WORDS() function reverses the order of a list of entries.
   </discussion>
   <example><![CDATA[
dim list as C = "a,b,a,c,d"
? *reverse_words(list, ",")
= "d,c,a,b,a"
]]></example>
   
